# My React Apps: Dog Finder & Color Factory

This repository contains two separate React applications: **Dog Finder** and **Color Factory**. Each app is designed to demonstrate different React functionalities, including routing, state management, and component-based design.

## Table of Contents

- [Dog Finder](#dog-finder)
  - [Overview](#overview)
  - [Setup & Running the App](#setup--running-the-app)
  - [Key Features](#key-features)
- [Color Factory](#color-factory)
  - [Overview](#overview-1)
  - [Setup & Running the App](#setup--running-the-app-1)
  - [Key Features](#key-features-1)

## Dog Finder

### Overview

The Dog Finder app allows users to view a list of dogs and see detailed information about each dog. The app uses React Router for navigation between different pages.

### Setup & Running the App

1. **Navigate to the Dog Finder directory**:
   ```bash
   cd DogFinder
   Install dependencies:
   ```

bash
Copy code
npm install
Start the application:

bash
Copy code
npm start
This will start both the frontend (React) and a backend server (using json-server), allowing you to interact with the app at http://localhost:3000/.

Key Features
View All Dogs: The homepage displays a list of all available dogs.
View Dog Details: Click on a dog's name to view detailed information, including the dog's name, age, and fun facts.
Navigation: Use React Router for seamless navigation between the list and detail views.
Color Factory
Overview
The Color Factory app allows users to add new colors to a list and view each color in its full display. The app demonstrates how to use forms, React state, and routing to create a dynamic and interactive application.

Setup & Running the App
Navigate to the Color Factory directory:

bash
Copy code
cd ColorFactory
Install dependencies:

bash
Copy code
npm install
Start the application:

bash
Copy code
npm run dev
The app will start on http://localhost:5173/ using Vite for a fast development experience.

Key Features
View All Colors: See a list of all the colors that have been added.
Add a New Color: Use the form to add a new color to the list.
View a Specific Color: Click on a color to see it displayed on its own page.
Navigation: Navigate easily between the list of colors and the add color form using React Router.
